    'definition_battle_variant2': 'The Minsk operation began on June 29, when the troops of the 3rd Belorussian and 1st Belorussian fronts attacked the enemy in a converging direction. Then, together with the troops of the 2nd Belorussian Front, the encirclement of Minsk was completed. The Belarusian partisans provided significant assistance to the troops, setting up ambushes on the path of retreat of the German forces, smashing headquarters, destroying bridges and crossings.',
    'definition_battle_variant1': 'The storming of the fortress, the city of Brest and the capture of bridges across the Western Bug and Mukhavets was entrusted to the 45th Infantry Division (45th Infantry Division) of the Wehrmacht, Major General Fritz Schlieper (about 15 thousand people) with reinforcement units. To conduct artillery preparation during the first five minutes of the division, mortar divisions of the 31st and 34th infantry divisions of the 12th Army Corps of the 4th Army were attached.',
    'definition_battle_variant3': 'Khatyn (possibly from Belorussian khata - house) is a village in Belarus destroyed on March 22, 1943 by a punitive detachment as revenge for the murder of several German servicemen. In accordance with the principle of collective punishment, 149 residents of Khatyn were burned alive or shot by the German army and the auxiliary police battalion for the possible assistance of the villagers to the partisans. The 118th Schutzmanschaft Battalion and the Dirlewanger Special SS Battalion took part in the punitive operation.',
    'definition_battle_variant4': 'Battle of Moscow (September 30, 1941 - April 20, 1942) - military operations of Soviet and German troops in the Moscow direction. It is divided into 2 periods: defensive (September 30 - December 4, 1941) and offensive, which consists of two stages: the counteroffensive (December 5, 1941 - January 7, 1942) and the Soviet offensive (January 7 - March 30, 1942). In Western historiography, the battle is known as Operation Typhoon.',
    'definition_battle_variant5': 'The Belarusian offensive operation "Bagration" is a strategic offensive operation of the Great Patriotic War, which was carried out on June 23 - August 29, 1944. Named in honor of the commander, who gained fame during the Patriotic War of 1812, P.I.Bagration. During the operation, the Soviet army inflicted the largest defeat on the German army in the entire military history of Germany, defeating the Wehrmacht Army Group Center. One of the largest military operations in the history of mankind.',
    'definition_battle_variant6': 'Battle of Kursk (July 5 - August 23, 1943; also known as the Battle of the Kursk Bulge) - a set of strategic defensive (July 5-23) and offensive (July 12 - August 23) operations of the Red Army in the Great Patriotic War in order to disrupt a major offensive forces of the Wehrmacht and defeat its strategic grouping. In historiography, it is considered the largest (greatest) tank battle in history. It was attended by about 2 million people, 6 thousand tanks, 4 thousand aircraft; the battle paved the way for the great Soviet offensive of 1944-45.',
    'definition_battle_variant7': 'Operation Iskra (German Zweite Ladoga-Schlacht - Second Battle of Lake Ladoga) is an offensive operation of Soviet troops during the Great Patriotic War, carried out from 12 to 30 January 1943 by the forces of the Leningrad and Volkhov fronts with the assistance of part of the forces of the Baltic Fleet, Ladoga military flotilla and long-range aviation with the aim of breaking the blockade of Leningrad.',
    'definition_battle_variant8': 'The Battle of Stalingrad is one of the most important and largest general battles of World War II and World War II between the Red Army and the Wehrmacht with the support of the armies of the Axis countries, which ended in victory for the USSR Armed Forces. The battle took place from July 17, 1942 to February 2, 1943 on the territory of modern Voronezh, Rostov, Volgograd regions and the Republic of Kalmykia.',
    'definition_battle_variant9': 'Battle of Rzhev - military operations of Soviet and German troops during the Great Patriotic War, which took place in the region of the Rzhev-Vyazemsky ledge from January 5, 1942 to March 21, 1943, with intervals from one and a half to three months. It ended with the retreat of the 9th Army of the Wehrmacht on March 5, 1943 from the Rzhev-Vyazemsky ledge.',
    'definition_battle_variant10': 'The Gomel-Rechitsa operation is an offensive operation of the troops of the Belorussian Front during the Great Patriotic War, carried out November 10 - November 30, 1943. As a result of the operation, Soviet troops broke through the enemys defenses in a strip 100 kilometers wide, and advanced 130 kilometers inland. On the morning of November 26, 1943, after fierce night battles, the city of Gomel was liberated.',
