    'text_email': 'Send us photos of the front letters of your ancestors by e-mail! We will definitely post them on our website!',
    'p1_p10': 'Good afternoon, dear parents.',
    'p2_p10': 'In the first lines of my letter I inform you that I am alive and almost healthy. The letter that you wrote on 16.06.45, I received and immediately answer. I received 4 letters from you in total, but not yet with photographs. But now I am starting to search through our postman. Dear mother, I received a letter from Misha Levchuk. And he wrote everything that interested me about Gelka. Dear mom, I’m wondering why you didn’t write right away that dad was disabled, and you are still writing, if you need money, we will send it. I would be glad to help you, but I myself have nothing. Soon I will get to the unit, I will bother about the vacation. And you try to get information about your state of health, it is possible that it will come out. I am thinking of staying to serve at the hospital, but I dont know if it will work out or not. You write that I, probably, have matured and got stronger, yes, you are right, I have matured, but I failed to get stronger, I am still as dry as I was.',
    'p3_p10': 'Dear parents, I am very worried that you are sick with me, and I cannot help. When I come, then it will be easier for you. Mom, I will ask you, please live more amicably, by doing this you will preserve your health. Be strong, I will return, and our life will become more beautiful and better. I live only for you, I am with you, and your life and health is everything for me. As soon as I arrive, I will put all my strength and health so that you, my dear ones, live calmly and peacefully. Well, as if everything. Say hello to Nyura and her family, Liza, Ivan, in general to all relatives and friends.',
    'p4_p10': 'I kiss you hard. Your son Boris Serebryakov. One p.m.',
    'p1_p9': 'Good afternoon, my dear Mom, Lucy, Igor and Lenochka !!!',
    'p2_p9': 'Dear ones, forgive me for not writing to you for so long. I received all your letters, for which many thanks. There are very few of them, my relatives. How you want to read your letter in your free minute, and even such as you write. After such a letter, you still become angry, even more desire to do more, to beat this reptile harder. Thank you, dear ones, for such letters. I am very pleased, I do not even know how to convey my joy that, although through letters, but you are with me. It is so good that all of you mothers, sisters, brothers, relatives, and friends together with us forge victory with us - this is another of the three guarantees of our victory. Of course, it is a pity to die, but at the same time I want to die, if your death brings the hour of victory closer, you, my family, will live wonderfully, you will sing wonderful songs about us and you will be with your head held high and you will say that your own son, brother, uncle died honestly in the struggle for the homeland, for liberation. My darlings, my deeds are good. Only I have not received letters from Kolya for a long time, and I myself have not written to him for a long time. How, dear, are you doing? How is your health, mommy?',
    'p3_p9': 'Write more and more often. Kisses tightly, your Zhora',
    'definition_test_variant1': 'At 4 oclock in the morning, without declaring war, Nazi Germany attacked the Soviet Union. Ahead was a long, difficult and bloody day - the first day of the war. The events of that day largely determined the course of further hostilities.',
    'definition_test_variant2': 'Films about war and Victory are small windows to another world where people lived with hope for a peaceful future. The heroes of these films have brought up more than one generation of our compatriots by their noble example.',
