    'defenition_belarus_remember': 'Those who do not remember the history of their country have no future. More than 75 years have passed, Belarus remembers and honors the feat of the dead and the living, famous and nameless Belarusians - soldiers of the Great Patriotic War, partisans, and underground fighters. Belarus remembers millions of citizens kidnapped in Nazi slavery, tortured in concentration camps and ghettos, remembers those who forged Victory behind enemy lines on their machines and liberated the country from Nazi invaders. Belarus remembers and honors the Great Victory, which united and will always unite people of different generations from young to old, no matter how much time has passed, it remembers all the defenders of the Fatherland without exception. We are faithful to this memory, the Belarusians keep it in every home, in every family. And the younger generation will not allow us to rewrite the real history of that terrible war and the heroism of our great-grandfathers, grandfathers, and fathers.',
    'title_brest': 'Brest Fortress',
    'title_kerch': 'Kerch',
    'title_kiev': 'Kiev',
    'title_sevastopol': 'Sevastopol',
    'title_smolensk': 'Smolensk',
