    'title_stalingrad': 'Stalingrad',
    'defenition_brest': 'Of all the cities of the Soviet Union, it was Brest that had the fate to take the first battle with the German invaders.',
    'defenition_kerch': 'Kerch was one of the first cities to be hit by the Nazi troops at the beginning of the war. During the entire war, the front line passed through the city four times and it was twice occupied by enemy troops.',
    'defenition_kiev': 'German troops launched a surprise air strike on Kiev on June 22, 1941 - in the very first hours of the war. On July 6, the City Defense Committee was created. From that day on, the heroic struggle for Kiev began, which lasted 72 days.',
    'defenition_sevastopol': 'By the beginning of World War II, the city of Sevastopol was the largest Soviet port on the Black Sea and the countrys main naval base.',
    'defenition_smolensk': 'With the outbreak of the Great Patriotic War, Smolensk found itself in the path of the main blow of the fascist troops moving towards Moscow.',
    'defenition_leningrad': 'Leningrad was a special city for the USSR, therefore, the plans of the Hitlerite command were the complete destruction of the city and the extermination of its population.',
    'defenition_minsk': 'From the first days of the Great Patriotic War, Minsk found itself in the very center of the battles. The advanced units of the Hitlerite army approached the city on June 26, 1941.',
    'defenition_moscow': 'In the aggressive plans of Nazi Germany, the capture of Moscow was of paramount importance, since it was with the fall of the capital that the complete victory of the German troops over the USSR was associated.',
    'defenition_odessa': 'In August 1941, Odessa was surrounded by German troops. The defense of Odessa lasted 73 days by the forces of the army and the peoples militia.',
    'defenition_tula': 'By October 1941, the fascist invaders, who dreamed of capturing Moscow, managed to advance quite far into the depths of Russia, which was explained by the great advantage in manpower and military equipment.',
    'defenition_murmansk': 'The military history of Murmansk began with the offensive in 1941 by the fascist German army in several directions at once. To seize the lands of the Soviet Arctic from the side of Norway and Finland, the "Norway" front was deployed.',
    'defenition_novorossiysk': 'After the Soviet troops thwarted the German plan for conducting offensive operations in the Caucasian direction, the Hitlerite command launched an attack on Novorossiysk in order to begin to gradually advance along the southern coast of the Black Sea with its capture.',
    'defenition_stalingrad': 'Stalingrad is one of the most famous and significant cities bearing the title of a hero city. In the summer of 1941, fascist German troops launched a massive offensive on the southern front, seeking to capture the Caucasus, Crimea, the Don region, the lower Volga and the Kuban - the most fertile lands of the USSR.',
